text: Edmond Joseph (Eddie) Gong (October 6, 1930 - May 19, 2015) was an American attorney and former politician in the state of Florida. He was the first Asian-American elected to the Florida House. He served as a Florida state senator from 1967 through 1971. He was also a member of Florida's House of Representatives from 1963 through 1966. Gong died at the age of 84 in Miami, Florida. ==References== Category:1930 births Category:2015 deaths Category:Politicians from Florida Category:Democratic Party (United States) politicians Category:Members of the Florida Legislature
